<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-10-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-10-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="1564" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1564">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/676.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Bonney</persName> to
                                    the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">San Luis Potosi</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-10-08">
                                        <hi rend="italic">October 8, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Please to request General Carranza, Vera Cruz, to instruct his
                                General M. Zapata in Tula, Tamaulipas, to respect all property there
                                belonging to Spanish Vice Consul of San Luis Potosí consisting of
                                hides, ixtle and plantation, now threatened by that General.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bonney.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>